{
  "text": "The chemical and nutritional composition, as well as the sensory profile of the plants, is determined by genetic and environmental factors and their interactions [CITATION_1] . In PDO or PGI products, the specific quality profile is conferred by the interaction between the genotype (i.e., landraces) and the environment (i.e., the historical area of production) [CITATION_2] , and research programs should identify the genetic and environmental factors underlying these traits. For this reason, it is important to conduct studies that increase our understanding of the factors influencing quality.",
